divs: sighting detailsi was driving home from the town of lake elsinore. turned up country club drive from lakeshore drive toward eastern hills. we have a lot of air traffic here because of near-by airport\sky-diving, hang-gliding, balloonists, private planes, military planes and copters etc., activities so, i'm very aware of what's in our sky. looked up and noticed bright silvery, shiny oval quite a distance up and high in sky. i slowed down and stopped to have a better look because object was not typically shaped. no wings, no tail, no sound. was not the usual "sky stuff" we see here. watched object for a few seconds as it sharply bobbed up and down while steadily moving toward the south-east. i turned away briefly, looked back and it had completely disappeared. eastern sky view is open to view planes for a long way out but there was no hint of the silver object. i continued on toward my home thinking.. "i believe i just saw a ufo". parked car approximately one minute later. went out back to search sky some more for object. found nothing as i viewed the entire eastern sky. object had been traveling silently toward the south-east. almost looked like who ever was piloting the object was moving it up and down as they flew along. what i mean is, a plane just moves along in a straight line. this object sort of "played" as it flew.
Summary: Saw shiny silvery object in eastern sky
